            <p>
                The dark side of the moon is riddled with craters with ridges so sharp that it would be dangerous for even a moon rover to traverse.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>The major difference between the near side and the dark side is the lack of <i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">maria</i> on the dark side.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </span>Scientists believe this is due to the thicker crust which is prohibiting the basaltic flows that are present on the near side.
            </p>
